FBIS4-30562 "dreas124_c_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 North Korea Pyongyang, Seoul Agree To Top-Level Talks Pyongyang, Seoul Agree To Top-Level Talks Radio Reports Preliminary Contact SK2806012494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 0110 GMT 28 Jun 94 SK2806012494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 0110 GMT 28 Jun 94 Korean BFN [Text] A preliminary contact for top-level talks between the North and the South has begun. A preliminary contact for top-level talks between the North and the South has begun in the South side area at Panmunjom at 1000 [0100 GMT] on 28 June. Kim Yong-sun, chairman of the Reunification Policy Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly and head of our delegation; An Pyong- su, vice chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland; Paek Nam-chun, chief councilor in the Administration Council; and the delegates from our side, attended the contact. The contact continues.
